66.4	The_Metamorphosis	The Metamorphosis	The Metamorphosis (German: ) is a novella by Franz Kafka, first published in 1915. It is often cited as one of the seminal works of fiction of the 20th century and is widely studied in colleges and universities across the western world. The story begins with a traveling salesman, Gregor Samsa, waking to find himself transformed into a monstrous insect-like creature.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/71/Metamorphosis.jpg
